### Elasticsearch Idiomatic API Requests
### Execute these requests using the VS Code REST Client or Visual Studio .http support.

@host = http://localhost:5000

### 1. Test Swagger Endpoint
GET {{host}}/swagger/v1/swagger.json
Accept: application/json

### 2. Flavorful Use Case: Full Text Search
# This endpoint executes a robust Multi-Match query against multiple fields 
# (Product Name, Company Name, Employee Name) simultaneously.
GET {{host}}/api/orders/search?q=Tofu
Accept: application/json

### 3. Flavorful Use Case: Analytics Aggregation
# This endpoint uses Elasticsearch Terms and Sum Aggregations to 
# dynamically calculate the top 5 customers by total order revenue.
GET {{host}}/api/analytics/top-customers
Accept: application/json

### 4. Flavorful Use Case: Exact Match Filtering
# Quickly retrieve all orders handled by a specific employee (EmployeeId: 1 = Nancy Davolio).
GET {{host}}/api/orders/employee/1
Accept: application/json

### 5. Advanced Feature: Simple Query String (Fuzziness & Synonyms)
# Retrieves records matching "cheese" with a fuzziness of 2 (matches "chees"), using the OR default operator.
GET {{host}}/api/orders/sqs?q=chees~2
Accept: application/json

### 6. Advanced Feature: Simple Query String (Targeted Fields & Prefix)
# Finds any order containing an item prefixed with "Tof" explicitly in the productName field.
GET {{host}}/api/orders/sqs?q=Tof*&fields=lines.product.productName
Accept: application/json

### 7. Advanced Feature: Simple Query String Compound (NOT Operator & Filters)
# Uses a compound query to find orders related to "seafood" but explicitly excludes anything with "crab"
# and restricts results to only those handled by employee 1.
GET {{host}}/api/orders/sqs/compound?q=seafood%20-crab&employeeId=1
Accept: application/json

### 8. The Ultimate Query-By-Example Custom DSL
# Translates an arbitrary JSON array of partial objects into a deeply nested Elasticsearch Bool query.
# This reads as: Find orders where (Customer Country is Germany AND Employee LastName is Davolio) 
#                OR (Customer Country is France)
POST {{host}}/api/orders/custom-dsl
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

[
  {
    "customer": { "country": "Germany" },
    "employee": { "lastName": "Davolio" }
  },
  {
    "customer": { "country": "France" }
  }
]
